# {{context|philosophy|logic}} A [[valid]] form of [[argument]] in which the [[consequent]] of a [[conditional]] [[proposition]] is [[deny|denied]], thus [[imply]]ing the denial of the [[antecedent]].  Modus tollens has this form:
#:1. If P, then Q.
#:2. Not Q.
#:3. Therefore, not P.

